  "prompt": "Do the prime minister of our country require visa to visit any country?",
  "response": "The requirement for a visa for a country's prime minister to visit another country depends on diplomatic agreements and treaties between the countries involved. In many cases, high-ranking officials like prime ministers may be granted special privileges or exemptions from regular visa requirements due to their status and the nature of their visit.\n\nFor example, if the prime minister is visiting a country with which their home country has strong diplomatic relations, they may not need a visa or may be granted a visa upon arrival. Additionally, for official state visits, arrangements are often made in advance to facilitate travel without the need for a traditional visa.\n\nHowever, it is important to note that these arrangements can vary widely depending on the specific countries and circumstances of the visit.",
